GLASGOW projects will receive &pound;400 million in funding for regeneration and development across the city.
The City Deal cash was outlined by Glasgow City Council’s Regeneration and Economy Committee for six draft plans on three projects.
Over the next decade, these include:
Councillor Gordon Matheson, leader of Glasgow City Council, said: “These tremendously exciting City Deal projects will help to transform Glasgow and its economy, bringing thousands of job during and after the construction periods and taking the city to the next economic level. These projects will help to tackle long-term economic issues and build a platform for future prosperity.”
The city centre will have an avenue of trees, new cycle routes will be created to link to the New South Glasgow Hospitals campus, and other projects will tap into the funds, part of &pound;500 million for City Deal across eight local authorities in Glasgow and Clyde Valley.
